---
import OdeLayout from '../../../layouts/OdeLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../../components/ode/Section.astro';
import DataTag from '../../../components/ode/DataTag.astro';
import CowGlyph from '../../../components/ode/CowGlyph.astro';
import LifecycleFlow from '../../../components/ode/LifecycleFlow.astro';
import { odeMeta, odeRoutes } from '../../../i18n/ode';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const m = odeMeta[lang].tracciabilita;
const r = odeRoutes[lang];
const g = r.glossario;

const layers = [
  {
    k: 'Mandatory layer',
    glyph: 'calf' as const,
    title: 'Cattle herd register',
    body: 'Every animal carries an individual identity: a double ear tag and a 14-character BDN code, unchanged from birth to death. Birth, movements and slaughter are recorded by EU and national law.',
    refs: 'Reg. EU 2016/429 · Implementing Reg. EU 2021/520 · D.Lgs 134/2022',
  },
  {
    k: 'Voluntary yet binding layer',
    glyph: 'cow' as const,
    title: 'DOP specification',
    body: 'The Parmigiano Reggiano specification binds the animal to a certified territory and diet: local forage, an absolute ban on silage, a district limited to five provinces. A nutritional ID card for the herd.',
    refs: 'Reg. EU 1151/2012 · Implementing Reg. EU 2025/661 · OCQ PR',
  },
];

const gaps = [
  {
    n: '01',
    problema: 'The break between stable and rendering',
    body: 'The ear tag identifies the single animal up to the abattoir. But at rendering the adipose tissue of many animals merges into lots: individual identity dissolves into the batch. The commercial document traces the lot of rendered fat, no longer the single animal or the DOP farm.',
    presidio: 'Chain-of-custody agreements with abattoirs and rendering plants that segregate lots by origin and document their geographic provenance.',
  },
  {
    n: '02',
    problema: 'The specification does not cover tallow',
    body: 'The DOP covers milk and cheese. No DOP certification extends to the fat: OdE cannot claim the DOP for its tallow, nor imply the fat is DOP-certified.',
    presidio: 'Communicate provenance from the district, never a DOP certification of the lipid product. Rigour in the claim as a form of credibility.',
  },
  {
    n: '03',
    problema: 'The cull cow may leave first',
    body: 'A cow that produced milk can be sold, fed differently and moved out of the district before slaughter, with events still logged in BDN. From a cow that produced milk is not the same as fed to specification until slaughter.',
    presidio: 'Define the claim precisely (from district cattle) and tie sourcing to animals slaughtered directly from the circuit.',
  },
  {
    n: '04',
    problema: 'The ABP category must be proven',
    body: 'Cosmetic tallow must be Category 3 material (low risk, from animals under ante and post-mortem control). Category 3 rendered fats need no chemical marker, which makes documentary separation from Cat. 1 and 2 even more crucial.',
    presidio: 'Prove Category 3 and physical and documentary separation across transport and processing: batch register, commercial document, plant approval.',
  },
  {
    n: '05',
    problema: 'A proprietary documentary layer is needed',
    body: 'No rule automatically links the tallow lot to the DOP origin. The gap between mandatory individual identity and the anonymous batch stays open: it is the exact point where a proprietary system creates value.',
    presidio: 'The Digital Lipid Passport rests on a contractual and information system built by OdE, voluntarily bridging the gap the law leaves open.',
  },
];
---
<OdeLayout title={m.title} description={m.description} lang={lang} active="tracciabilita">
  <header class="hero">
    <p class="ode-eyebrow">Traceability</p>
    <h1>Provenance as verifiable proof</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The dairy cows of the Parmigiano Reggiano circuit are among the most documented and regulated
      cattle in Europe. A double regulatory layer converges on them, making OdE’s
      <a href={`${g}#sego`}>tallow</a> traceable from the barn, animal by animal, along the whole chain.
      This is the real asset underpinning the <a href={`${g}#passaporto`}>Digital Lipid Passport</a>.
    </p>
  </header>

  <Section n="1" title="The double regulatory layer">
    <p>
      Two independent systems overlap on the same animal: a mandatory one fixing its individual identity,
      and a voluntary yet binding one certifying its territory and diet. Together they build a highly
      documented and auditable provenance.
    </p>
    <div class="layers">
      {layers.map((l) => (
        <article class="layer">
          <div class="layer-head">
            <CowGlyph variant={l.glyph} size={40} class="layer-glyph" />
            <span class="layer-k">{l.k}</span>
          </div>
          <h3>{l.title}</h3>
          <p>{l.body}</p>
          <p class="layer-refs">{l.refs}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section n="2" title="The life path of a DOP cow">
    <p>
      From birth to slaughter traceability is strong and mandatory: every animal has a documented history.
      Then, between leaving the certified stable and the lot of rendered fat, individual identity weakens
      and dissolves. It is in that grey area that OdE plugs in.
    </p>
    <LifecycleFlow lang={lang} />
    <p class="note">
      <DataTag kind="fonte" label="OdE regulatory research on DOP traceability; texts cited on EUR-Lex and Consorzio Parmigiano Reggiano" />
      BDN herd register, Parmigiano Reggiano specification, Reg. (EC) 1069/2009 and Reg. (EU) 142/2011 on
      animal by-products. Terms: <a href={`${g}#soa`}>ABP</a>, <a href={`${g}#sego`}>tallow</a>,
      <a href={`${g}#passaporto`}>Lipid Passport</a>.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section n="3" title="Where traceability breaks">
    <p>
      The grey areas are OdE’s operating agenda, and each has a precise safeguard. Naming them clearly is
      already part of the rigour a demanding audience rewards.
    </p>
    <div class="gaps">
      {gaps.map((gp) => (
        <article class="gap">
          <span class="gap-n">{gp.n}</span>
          <div class="gap-body">
            <h3>{gp.problema}</h3>
            <p>{gp.body}</p>
            <p class="gap-presidio"><span class="gap-pk">Safeguard</span> {gp.presidio}</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section n="4" title="The boundaries of the specification">
    <div class="honesty">
      <p>
        The specification governs milk and cheese. The animal’s end of life (cull cows, the typical source
        of tallow) sits outside its perimeter: the text itself confirms it, and the DOP control plan
        covers farms, dairies, ageing warehouses, grating and portioning, while abattoirs and rendering
        plants fall under general law.
      </p>
      <p>
        Two planes must stay distinct. The specification bans <a href={`${g}#sego`}>tallow</a> as an
        ingredient in the cows’ diet (the input side), and leaves out tallow as an output product at the
        animal’s end of life (the output side). OdE sits, clearly, on the second plane.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section n="5" title="Where OdE plugs in">
    <p>
      Since no rule links the fat lot to the DOP origin, that link must be built. OdE builds it with three
      tools that stitch the grey area back together, turning an already documented provenance into
      verifiable, sellable proof.
    </p>
    <div class="solutions">
      <article class="sol">
        <span class="sol-k">Chain of custody</span>
        <p>Selection of partner abattoirs and rendering plants, lot segregation by origin, collection of
        geographic provenance and Category 3 evidence.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="sol">
        <span class="sol-k">Digital Lipid Passport</span>
        <p>The proprietary documentary layer binding identity, origin, spectra and analysis of the lot in
        one object: register and dossier at once, ready for the incoming <a href={`${g}#dpp`}>Digital
        Product Passport</a>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="sol">
        <span class="sol-k">AMSA</span>
        <p>The <a href={`${g}#amsa`}>spectroscopic agent</a> reads each lot and certifies profile,
        stability and suitability: the lipid signature becomes an objective check downstream of the chain.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <p class="thesis">
      A mandatory herd register, a feeding specification and a defined geographic area give a highly
      documented and auditable provenance. OdE builds the Passport on public, verifiable data, with a
      degree of regulatory robustness rare in the lipid-ingredients market. Provenance is a verifiable
      datum that withstands the audit.
    </p>
    <p class="note">
      For the terms on this page, see the <a href={g}>glossary</a>:
      <a href={`${g}#bdn`}>BDN register</a>, <a href={`${g}#marca`}>ear tag</a>,
      <a href={`${g}#riforma`}>cull cow</a>, <a href={`${g}#custodia`}>chain of custody</a>,
      <a href={`${g}#disciplinare`}>DOP specification</a>, <a href={`${g}#soa`}>ABP Category 3</a>.
      See also the <a href={r.normativa}>Regulatory Clock</a>.
    </p>
  </Section>
</OdeLayout>

<style>
  .hero { max-width: 46rem; padding: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 1rem; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--body); }
  .lede a, .note a, .thesis a, .honesty a, .sol a {
    color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .note { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; max-width: 44rem; }

  .layers { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(16rem, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.2rem; }
  .layer { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-radius: var(--ode-radius); padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem; }
  .layer-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .layer-glyph { color: var(--accent); flex: none; }
  .layer-k { font-family: var(--ode-font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--accent); }
  .layer h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
  .layer p { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.5; }
  .layer-refs { font-family: var(--ode-font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.4; }

  .gaps { display: grid; gap: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1.2rem; }
  .gap {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr; gap: 0 0.9rem;
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--ode-radius); padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem;
  }
  .gap-n { font-family: var(--ode-font-mono); font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .gap-body h3 { font-size: 1.02rem; font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
  .gap-body p { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 42rem; }
  .gap-presidio {
    background: var(--green-soft); border-radius: var(--ode-radius-sm);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.7rem; font-size: 0.86rem !important; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }
  .gap-pk {
    font-family: var(--ode-font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--accent);
    margin-right: 0.3rem;
  }

  .honesty { border-left: 3px solid var(--rule); padding: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem 1.1rem; max-width: 44rem; }
  .honesty p { font-size: 0.96rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .solutions { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(14rem, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin: 1.2rem 0; }
  .sol { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-radius: var(--ode-radius); padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem; }
  .sol-k { display: block; font-weight: 500; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .sol p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5; }

  .thesis {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--green-border);
    padding: 0.7rem 0 0.7rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--green-soft);
    border-radius: 0 var(--ode-radius) var(--ode-radius) 0;
    font-size: 1.02rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink); max-width: 46rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .gap { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .gap-n { margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  }
</style>
